results.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES--Like thousands of other Californians, Philip Reid, a salesman who lives in the San Fernando Valley, was trapped in a long line waiting for gasoline last week. "Look at all those cais," he said, looking up from a book he had brought to while away the time. "You know what's happening? We're witnessing the demise of the American way of life. The future is here."
